      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 6
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_6_listing_6",
      "firm_id": "sybil_6",
      "description": "Hey there! Honestly, I\u2019m a bit sad to see this beauty go, but it\u2019s time for someone else to enjoy it. This car is in absolutely incredible shape\u2014seriously, it looks and smells like it just rolled off the showroom floor! It\u2019s been babied since day one, kept in a garage, and it drives like an absolute dream. No scratches, no dings, just pure perfection. If you're looking for a ride that\u2019s basically brand new without the brand-new price tag, this is the one for you. Come take a look, you won't be disappointed!",
      "price": 45500.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 6
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offering a museum-grade 2001 Acura Integra Type R in iconic Championship White. This DC2 remains in its factory-delivered configuration, featuring the high-compression B18C5 engine with hand-polished intake ports and an 8,400 RPM redline. The close-ratio 5-speed manual gearbox shifts with surgical precision, utilizing the original helical limited-slip differential (LSD) to manage torque through the corners. The seam-welded chassis and double-wishbone suspension maintain absolute structural integrity, free of any aftermarket interference. All matching-number VIN tags are present on original body panels, and the interior retains its factory-spec Alcantara bolsters and titanium shift knob. A rare opportunity to acquire a pinnacle of front-wheel-drive engineering in concours condition.",
